---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Ui.astro';
---

<Base title="Typography">
  <h1>Typography &amp; prose</h1>
  <p>
    Monospace everywhere, hierarchy from size and weight — no borders, no
    radius. The type scale carries headings to body; <code>.mk-prose</code>
    handles article-style long-form content.
  </p>

  <section class="mk-card">
    <h2>Type scale</h2>
    <p>Headings and body text, top to bottom. Set in <code>--mk-font-body</code>.</p>

    <div class="specimen">
      <div class="specimen__row">
        <span class="specimen__label">h1 / 3xl</span>
        <h1 style="margin: 0;">Watchlist</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="specimen__row">
        <span class="specimen__label">h2 / 2xl</span>
        <h2 style="margin: 0;">Currently airing</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="specimen__row">
        <span class="specimen__label">h3 / xl</span>
        <h3 style="margin: 0;">Season 2</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="specimen__row">
        <span class="specimen__label">h4 / lg</span>
        <h4 style="margin: 0;">Episode notes</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="specimen__row">
        <span class="specimen__label">body / md</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog — 0123456789.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="specimen__row">
        <span class="specimen__label">small / sm</span>
        <small>Last watched 3 days ago.</small>
      </div>
    </div>

    <pre><code>&lt;h1&gt;Watchlist&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Currently airing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Body copy in the mono stack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;small&gt;Caption text.&lt;/small&gt;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mk-card" style="margin-block-start: var(--mk-space-5);">
    <h2>Prose</h2>
    <p>
      Wrap article content in <code>.mk-prose</code> for paragraph rhythm,
      lists, code, blockquotes, and inline elements — all tonal, all
      border-free.
    </p>

    <div class="mk-prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Severance</strong> follows a team whose work selves and home
        selves are surgically split. You can mark episodes watched, rate them,
        and leave a <em>note</em> per episode.
      </p>

      <h3>Watch states</h3>
      <p>An episode moves through a small set of states:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>unwatched — the default</li>
        <li>watched — counts toward season progress</li>
        <li>
          skipped — excluded from progress
          <ul>
            <li>recaps and specials skip by default</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Marking via the API</h3>
      <p>
        Toggle a state with <code>PATCH /episodes/:id</code>. The response
        echoes the updated record:
      </p>
      <pre><code>PATCH /episodes/8f21e
&#123; "state": "watched", "rating": 5 &#125;
=&gt; 200 &#123; "id": "8f21e", "state": "watched", "rating": 5 &#125;</code></pre>

      <blockquote>
        <p>
          Progress is computed, never stored — skipped episodes simply drop out
          of the denominator.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Prefer the keyboard? Press <kbd>W</kbd> to mark watched, or
        <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>S</kbd> to skip.
      </p>

      <small>Counts refresh on the next sync.</small>
    </div>

    <pre><code>&lt;article class="mk-prose"&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Body copy with &lt;code&gt;inline code&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;A pull quote.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Press &lt;kbd&gt;W&lt;/kbd&gt; to mark watched.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/article&gt;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <style>
    .specimen {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--mk-space-4);
    }

    .specimen__row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: var(--mk-space-2) var(--mk-space-4);
    }

    .specimen__label {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      min-width: 7rem;
      font-size: var(--mk-text-xs);
      color: var(--mk-color-text-muted);
    }
  </style>
</Base>
